value.0: Styrkarr is a large man, easily one of the largest in Howness. He is also one of the loudest. Scars and fresh wounds alike riddle this man's body and it doesn't seem like he's the type of man to back down from a fight. Be wary with what you say to him lest he decides to use the large axe he wields on you next.

Hildungr is on the shorter side but his rage makes up the difference. Angry, grumpy, upset - however you want to put it, there is no doubt that this man has serious anger issues. And a drinking problem. He's hardly ever seen without a mug of some type of alcohol in one of his hands.

With a perpetual scowl on his face, Eirikr is yet another man within the Marauder who clearly has an anger issue. And with a large greataxe that has seen more than enough use strapped to his back, it probably wouldn't be wise to rile him up. He tends to lean against the nearest wall and watch everyone around him with a hawk-like gaze.

Olina is large for a woman - scarly so. Strong like an ox and just as hard-headed, this woman likes to stick close to the Brawler's Ring and watches whatever fights break out with a mirthful light in her eyes. She usually participates in said fights, too. Her weapon of choice is, oddly enough, a double headed axe. It's a weapon she wields with ease.

Leaning on the railing, Anette watches the Brawler's Ring intensely. Her foot would bounce with either excitement or restraint - which one is hard to determine - whenever a brawl comes about. She's one of the first to yell loudly in favor of who she wants to win.
With a slur in his speech, red in his cheeks and nose, and a stumble in his step, Dagr clearly enjoys his drink a little too much.
This man has seen far too many bar fights to even care anymore. His lack of caring shows, too. Folki looks haggard, worn down, but his eyes do twinkle whenever a rather good fight breaks out.
Jorunnr is the pretty waitress of the Thirsty Marauder. She does her job with ease, bustling to and fro to serve the tavern's customers with a bright, dazzling smile on her face.

Alrik steadily plays his lute regardless of the fights down below. He's up this high for a reason, after all. The lute he holds has a few dents on the body, probably from beating a few drunkards away.
With a set of panpipes in her hands, Arippikka keeps up with the rest of the musicians.
Naakve, while enjoying the drums he plays, often seems to get bored. He yawns loudly, which earns him a few glares from the other musicians.
